You could do it [like this](https://svelte.dev/repl/f94bc4f69d2b4629ba4f5052c727b847?version=3.12.1):

```html
&lt;script&gt;
	import ChartA from &#39;./ChartA.svelte&#39;
	import ChartB from &#39;./ChartB.svelte&#39;
	import ChartC from &#39;./ChartC.svelte&#39;
	let charts = [
		ChartA,
		ChartB,
		ChartC
	];
	let events = [];
&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;style&gt;
	.icon{
		width:60px;
		height:30px;
		background-color:grey;
	}
&lt;/style&gt;

{#each charts as chart, i}
	&lt;div class=&quot;wrapper&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div class=&quot;icon&quot; on:click={e=&gt;events[i] = e}&gt;Click&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
			&lt;svelte:component this={charts[i]} event={events[i]}/&gt;
		&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
{/each}
```

Passing events around as data would be a bit unusual though. It would be more idiomatic to set some state in the parent component in response to the event, and pass that state down.

[Alternatively](https://svelte.dev/repl/8b97f00e55be46daae9db8db5f0cf973?version=3.12.1), if the child components *do* need to respond to events themselves you could take this approach...

```html
&lt;script&gt;
	import ChartA from &#39;./ChartA.svelte&#39;
	import ChartB from &#39;./ChartB.svelte&#39;
	import ChartC from &#39;./ChartC.svelte&#39;
	let charts = [
		ChartA,
		ChartB,
		ChartC
	];
	let instances = []; 
&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;style&gt;
	.icon{
		width:60px;
		height:30px;
		background-color:grey;
	}
&lt;/style&gt;

{#each charts as chart, i}
	&lt;div class=&quot;wrapper&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div class=&quot;icon&quot; on:click={e =&gt; instances[i].handle(e)}&gt;Click&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
			&lt;svelte:component
				this={charts[i]}
				bind:this={instances[i]}
			/&gt;
		&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
{/each}
```

...where each child component exports a `handle` method:

```html
&lt;script&gt;
	let event;
	export function handle(e){
		event = e;
	};
&lt;/script&gt;
```

