I&#39;ve learned how to avoid this ( though still not clear why)
 `plt.tight_layout()` should behind `plt.savefig(&#39;path+name.jpg&#39;, bbox_inches=&#39;tight&#39;)`, then `views` and `tables` will not be overlapped.

 - If `plt.tight_Layout()` is before `plt.savefig`, what we can see is functiong can only **tight** the `viewes` excluding `tables`(tables very likely will be overlapped), so does the pictures created by `plt.savefig()`;
 - if we set `plt.rcParams[&#39;figure.autolayout&#39;] = True` instead of `plt.tight_layout()`, well, `viewes` and `tables` is fine in the `figure window`, however, the `tables` were overlapped still in the picture created by `plt.savefig()`;
 - if we move the `plt.savefig()`,

 -- `plt.tight_layout()` can only zoom the `viewes` excluding `tables`;

 -- `plt.rcParams[&#39;figure.autolayout&#39;]=True` can zoom both of `viewes` and `tables` in the `figure` window.

